    <h1 id="english">What's up <%= @user.username %>?</h1>

    <p>Congrats! Your request to manage <%= @event.name %> has been approved by our moderators. You can now edit your shows’ information at anytime by clicking ‘edit this event’ at the very bottom of the event page (please note, you must be logged in to see this option). To see a list of all the events / venues / band profiles you manage, simply log in and go to ‘Your Page’ (under ‘account’ in the main menu, again you must be logged in to see this).</p>

<p>Do you find it really annoying & time consuming to have to create loads of different event pages for all your different social network site and cafes etc? Yeh, we thought so! We do too, so to help you out, we have created a feature on DoIndie that we hope will save you all that time and effort. Head to your event page and scroll down to the bottom. Hit the ‘Create Text Version’ button and DoIndie will create a text only version of your event. Simply copy this text and paste it into your facebook event page or cafe posting. Easy! No need to type the information over and over again!</p>

